In your drunk haze, you saw that one person, the one reason why you're drinking again tonight, smile in front of you and watch you drink another shot of soju.


"How does it taste?" was a question that followed the moment you placed the glass back on the table.

Slowly, that person's illusion fades... and what's been left was an empty seat.

"It's bitter." you answered.

To: ytchannel@gmail.com

Subject: Sweet Night

To whom it may concern,

A video of a song produced and composed by BTS’ V, ‘Sweet Night’ (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N5ShoQimivM), has recently been released on your platform (Youtube). While listening to it, we noticed that the channel that shared the video did not include ‘V’ as the artist in the descriptions, which gives him, 0 youtube points for the charts, despite the video being in the ‘Music’ category.

Today, an announcement made by the channel (Vlending) was released stating that if the artist name was not showed in the description of the video, it was because the artist was not working under their agency which made him not displayed for users but also for the operating account.

Furthermore, only 1 day left for tracking for Hot100 and this technical problem can damage the charting spot of ‘Sweet Night’. The rest of BTS’ fanbase and I ask you to please try to fix this problem as soon as possible, as BTS V had worked very hard for this music and we want his efforts to be acknowledged.

Thank you in advance

A video of a song produced and composed by BTS’ V, ‘Sweet Night’ (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N5ShoQimivM), has recently been released on your platform (Youtube). While listening to it, we noticed that the channel that shared the video did not include ‘V’ as the artist in the descriptions, which gives him, 0 youtube points for the charts, despite the video being in the ‘Music’ category.

Today, an announcement made by the channel (Vlending) was released stating that if the artist name was not showed in the description of the video, it was because the artist was not working under their agency which made him not displayed for users but also for the operating account.

Furthermore, only 1 day left for tracking for Hot100 and this technical problem can damage the charting spot of ‘Sweet Night’. The rest of BTS’ fanbase and I ask you to please try to fix this problem as soon as possible, as BTS V had worked very hard for this music and we want his efforts to be acknowledged.

Thank you in advance
